Backport PHP 8.6 build support onto the 3.5.3 release. Xdebug master
(3.6-dev) supports PHP 8.6, but no release ships it yet. This carries the
minimal source changes:
  - config.m4: relax the upper PHP version bound to < 8.7.0
  - INI_STR() -> zend_ini_string_literal() (macro removed in 8.6)
  - zend_ini_string() now returns const char*
  - internal_function.arg_info[].name is now zend_string* -> zend_string_copy()
  - ZSTR_INIT_LITERAL() with a variable -> zend_string_init()
  - WRONG_PARAM_COUNT -> zend_wrong_param_count() + RETURN_THROWS()
  - zval_dtor() -> zval_ptr_dtor_nogc() (alias removed in 8.6)

Refs:
  https://github.com/xdebug/xdebug/pull/1075
  https://github.com/xdebug/xdebug/commit/68c8a647b (version constraints)
